differences.text: What is a savings account? Savings accounts are a great solution for customers with a specific need or goal even if they also have a Money Market or CD. They allow customers to designate funds in individual accounts for a specific goal separate from their checking account. Common goals include; an emergency fund for unexpected expenses, vacation savings, holiday savings, home improvements, taxes, and saving for a new car among others. Read more about savings accounts and how they work . How do I open an account? Depending on your preference, you can apply for a Citizens savings account online, over the phone, or at any Citizens branch . To apply online, just select the appropriate link from the top of this page and find the account you wish to open. You will then see instructions about applying online. What is the minimum deposit to open a savings account? You may open a Citizens savings account with any amount. Take advantage of all the seamless tools and benefits to help maintain your financial goals and balances. What is APY? Annual Percentage Yield (APY) expresses an annual rate of return taking into account the effect of interest compounding. Are there any transaction limits on a savings account? Citizens does not limit transactions, including withdrawals, on savings accounts. Please refer to the Fees and Features Guide for additional information. How do I sign up for Citizens Savings Tracker? All you need to get started is an eligible Citizens Personal Savings or Money Market Account. If you want to take advantage of Round Ups 2 , you will also need an eligible Citizens Personal Checking Account. Download the Citizens Mobile Banking App* and register for mobile banking Select the "Financial Wellbeing" section in the app's menu and create a goal Discover more benefits of Citizens Savings Tracker® . 3

What is a money market account? A money market account is a variable APY account similar to a savings account which may earn a higher interest rate compared to savings for customers who do not need frequent access to their funds. Click here for more information about money market accounts. How can I monitor my money market account balance? Monitor and access your account anytime, anywhere with Citizens Mobile † and Online Banking. Download our 24/7 mobile app and learn more here . Do I have to maintain a minimum balance in my money market account? While we don't require a minimum balance to open, some accounts and/or promotional offers may have requirements that must be satisfied. See your promo offer for more details. What is APY? Annual Percentage Yield (APY) expresses an annual rate of return taking into account the effect of compounding. Click here for more information on Annual Percentage Yield. What is compound interest? Compound interest is the concept of adding accumulated interest back to the principal, so that interest is earned on interest from that moment on. Are there any transaction limits on a money market account? Unlimited deposits, in-branch or ATM transactions. We limit certain types of transactions to no more than 6 per statement period, including telephone transfers, online transfers, automatic interest transfers, preauthorized or automatic debits, preauthorized transfers, outgoing wire transfers and checks, debit card transactions or similar orders to a third party from the money market. If you exceed these limits 3 times or more during any consecutive 12-statement period, we will, as applicable, transfer the funds in your money market account to a checking account that does not pay interest. We may, however, transfer your funds sooner if you significantly exceed these transfer limits in any one statement period. Please refer to the Fees and Features Guide for additional information. Please note that withdrawals and transfers made at our branches or ATMs do not count against these limits. What is the minimum deposit amount to open a money market account? You may open a Citizens Money Market account with any amount. Take advantage of all the seamless tools and benefits to help maintain your financial goals and balances.

Safety and security Bank securely with 24/7 fraud monitoring and FDIC insurance . 3 Personalized guidance Would you like more details from one of our bankers? Schedule an appointment . Waive monthly maintenance fees We provide simple ways to waive your monthly maintenance fees.

What is a Certificate of Deposit (CD)? CDs are similar to savings accounts, but they are set to a fixed term (usually ranging from one month to ten years) and a fixed interest rate. It is expected that a CD be held to the end of the term, at which time the money may be withdrawn with the accrued interest. Early withdrawals of the principal balance may result in a fee, so ensure you will not need access to these funds for the term of the account before opening your CD. What is APY? Annual Percentage Yield (APY) expresses an annual rate of return taking into account the effect of compounding. Find out more about Annual Percentage Yield (APY). What is compound interest? Compound interest is the concept of adding accumulated interest back to the principal, so that interest is earned on interest from that moment on. What is an interest rate? An interest rate is the rate at which a financial institution agrees to pay you back for holding your money. Can I add additional funds to my certificate of deposit account? No, once your CD account is opened you cannot add additional funds to the account. After your CD account reaches maturity, you will have a 10-day grace period where you can add additional funds to your renewing CD account. What is the penalty for early withdrawal before CD maturity? If you withdraw the principal balance from your CD prior to maturity, you will be charged an early withdrawal penalty based on the term of your CD account. The applicable early withdrawal penalties are as follows: Short-term CD (Less than one year) - 90 days interest on withdrawal amount, or half the remaining interest to be earned, whichever is greater. Plus a Transaction Penalty - $50 Long-term CD (one year or longer) - 180 days interest on withdrawn amount, or half the remaining interest to be earned, whichever is greater. Plus a Transaction Penalty - $50 You can withdraw interest credited to your CD account before the maturity of the term of your CD without bank penalty. What happens when my CD matures? We will provide you with a CD Maturity notice 35 days prior to your CD account’s maturity date. The maturity date is the last day of your CD account’s term. There is a 10-day grace period that begins the day after your maturity date. During this 10-day grace period you have the following options: Renew your CD with the same term or a different term (if renewing you can add additional funds); Request a partial withdrawal of funds from your account without penalty; or Close your CD by withdrawing all of the funds from your account without penalty

How do I open a checking account? Depending on your preference, you can apply for a Citizens checking account online, over the phone, or at any Citizens branch . To apply online , just select the appropriate link from the top of this page and find the account you wish to open. You will then see instructions about applying online. How do I avoid overdrawing my checking account? Knowing how much money is available in your account is critical to avoiding overdraft situations. Citizens gives you tools that make it easy, such as Online and Mobile Banking 3 , and account alerts. Learn how to manage overdrafts and avoid fees by viewing our Overdraft Choices . What is the CitizensPlus* loyalty program? CitizensPlus ® is a benefit-rich loyalty program available only with Citizens Quest ® Checking and Citizens Private Client ® Checking accounts. As your relationship with Citizens grows, you get more benefits, rewards, and personalized advice. No additional enrollment is needed. How do I set up direct deposit and what kind of information is required? There are two options for setting up direct deposit online or with a direct deposit form from your employer. You will need to provide the following: Our bank routing number . This nine-digit number is found on the bottom left of your checks. Your checking account number. It can be found on the bottom of the check directly to the right of the routing number. A voided check. This will allow the employer to verify the above information. Write “VOID” in large letters in ink across the check, covering most lines so that nothing else can be written in on the check. Your branch address. You can find this information online, but you could also call a representative. More information on direct deposit No checks? No problem you can find your routing number online. Still have questions? More information on routing numbers . How do I upgrade my account to Citizens Quest® or Citizens Private Client® Checking? Go into your nearest branch or call 1-877-360-2472 How do I update my name and address in the system Simply call us at 1-800-922-9999 , visit any Citizens branch , or use the Change of Address feature of Online Banking .

Click here for more information about money market accounts. How can I monitor my money market account balance? Monitor and access your account anytime, anywhere with Citizens Mobile † and Online Banking. Download our 24/7 mobile app and learn more here . Do I have to maintain a minimum balance in my money market account? While we don't require a minimum balance to open, some accounts and/or promotional offers may have requirements that must be satisfied. See your promo offer for more details. What is APY? Annual Percentage Yield (APY) expresses an annual rate of return taking into account the effect of compounding. Click here for more information on Annual Percentage Yield. What is compound interest? Compound interest is the concept of adding accumulated interest back to the principal, so that interest is earned on interest from that moment on. Are there any transaction limits on a money market account? Unlimited deposits, in-branch or ATM transactions. We limit certain types of transactions to no more than 6 per statement period, including telephone transfers, online transfers, automatic interest transfers, preauthorized or automatic debits, preauthorized transfers, outgoing wire transfers and checks, debit card transactions or similar orders to a third party from the money market. If you exceed these limits 3 times or more during any consecutive 12-statement period, we will, as applicable, transfer the funds in your money market account to a checking account that does not pay interest. We may, however, transfer your funds sooner if you significantly exceed these transfer limits in any one statement period. Please refer to the Fees and Features Guide for additional information. Please note that withdrawals and transfers made at our branches or ATMs do not count against these limits. What is the minimum deposit amount to open a money market account? You may open a Citizens Money Market account with any amount. Take advantage of all the seamless tools and benefits to help maintain your financial goals and balances. Have more questions?
